Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1265,1974]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1841,1866]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Etymology.</emphasis>
A noun from Latin for &quot;perpendicular&quot; referring to the roughly 
<number box="[1099,1129,1842,1866]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" value="90.0">90</number>
° angled turn the oviscape membrane striations take from anterior to posterior end.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
